# React Patterns

<version>1.0.0</version>

## Context

- @.cursor/rules/nextjs.mdc - Next.js patterns
- @.cursor/rules/global-css.mdc - CSS configuration
- @.cursor/rules/tailwind-v4.mdc - Tailwind v4 features
- When creating or modifying React components
- When defining component props and their types
- Applies to both functional and class components

## Requirements

- Always use destructured props in function parameters
- Define TypeScript types inline with the destructured props
- Avoid creating separate interfaces for component props
- Avoid non-destructured props that require additional destructuring inside the component
- Use available UI components from the component library
- Use CSS variables from globals.css for consistent theming
- Use Tailwind v4: [tailwind-v4.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/tailwind-v4.mdc)
- DO NOT add icon margin in Button, DropdownMenuItem: use gap-2 instead
- Use custom breakpoint syntax for responsive design:
  - Use `@xl:` instead of `sm:`
  - Use `@3xl:` instead of `md:`
  - Use `@5xl:` instead of `lg:`
  - Use `@max-xl:` instead of `max-sm:`
  - Use `@max-3xl:` instead of `max-md:`
  - Use `@max-5xl:` instead of `max-lg:`

